This practice round fires an 11 grain hard plastic bullet at well over 4000 feet per second. So, to use a cliche, that makes them "priceless" to some of us.

postcontent:
For sale is a 1916 Bulgarian capured Mosin M91.  This has the pinged receiver, "Circle B" mark and pinecone stamp on the stock that show it was a Bulgarian captured rifle.  
pictures here.

http://www.flickr.com/photos/61095014@N03/sets/REDACTED7190606/

The bolt in the pictures is no the one that came with the rifle, or included in the sale, but I have put many rounds through this rifle without incident.  The bolt and floorplate however, are not matched.  Although there is some wear to the wood and the bore shows signs of wear (lands and grooves are strong, but is not bright and shiny) for being almost 100 years old this rifle is in excellent condition. 

It is missing one of the sight acjustment buttons and the cleaning rod.

If you're asking yourself why you would buy this rifle for $200 instead of one of the shiny M91/30s at fleet farm for $90, you probably aren't a collector.  The M91s are getting VERY hard to come by, especially the ones with such a rich history as this one.

$200 firm, will consider trade for HD shotty.  

I will require to see a valid driver's license and either a purchase permit or permit to carry.  I realize this is not required by law, but it is required for my peace of mind.  Also, I wil not sell to an end buyer that is not a MN resident, and will not ship or travel outside of the Mpls/Twin Cities area or sell to a "middle man". Please feel free to ask any questions and I will respond to them as quickly as possible.

title: For Sale:  Makarov Pistol - Russian Hi-Cap w/3 mags, ammo, holster & accessories
postcontent:
For sale is a Makarov pistol made in Russia by Imez and imported during the 90's by KBI. This particular pistol is the hi-capacity version that uses a 10 round double stack magazine. There were far fewer of these brought over than the standard single stack model.

I am the original owner of this pistol and it has been fired, but not much. I've always been amazed at how accurate this little pistol was. In terms of accuracy, durability and reliability this Russian pistol is at least as good or perhaps even better than any of the other Makarovs available. It is in excellent condition and the bore is "mirror" bright without any blemishes at all. It's chambered in the 9x18 Makarov round.

Pistol comes with:

It's original factory box which is also in excellent condition
All factory literature including instruction manual, warranty card, safety pamphlet, & hang tag
Factory furnished cleaning rod and Makarov tool
An original cold war era leather holster along with a matching leather lanyard strap
3 double stack magazines that sell for $75+ each on eBay & GunBroker if you can find them
5 boxes (250 rounds) of Silver Bear ammo with 94 grain FMJ bullets.

Price for everything listed above is $600. FTF with pickup in Brandon. Must be 21 or older and a Florida resident to purchase. Proper ID is required. Bill of sale will be provided.
